properties.areaDesc: Waters from San Mateo point to the Mexican Border Extending 30 to 60 nm out including San Clemente Island; Coastal Waters from San Mateo Point to the Mexican Border and out to 30 nm
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 9 at 7:29AM PST until January 9 at 9:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY TODAY...

.Northwest winds gusting to 25 kt, or locally 30 kt, will generate
conditions hazardous to small craft through this evening.

* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 25 kt, and up to 30 kt in the
outer waters. Seas of 6 to 11 feet expected.

* WHERE...Waters from San Mateo point to the Mexican Border
Extending 30 to 60 nm out including San Clemente Island and
Coastal Waters from San Mateo Point to the Mexican Border and
out to 30 nm.

* WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 9 PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A short-period wind swell will produce
rough and steep combined seas.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM PST THIS EVENING
